      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;With no snare, root or slows soloing a mage is not a proposition for the weak of heart. But I love to do it. Is it mana intesive? Yes. Are you going to take a few licks now and again? Sure.&amp;nbsp;But with the Elixir of Clarity and Healing&amp;nbsp;potions now,&amp;nbsp;mana regen and healing&amp;nbsp;aren't that much of a problem anymore.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I pull with the Malo line and then send the pet when the mob gets to my kill spot. After the pet has good agro I throw my Elemental DoT spell then heal the pet and wait until the mob is down to about 30% beofore lobbing in my big nuke to finish it off. While I can solo Yellow cons with my Chanter and even Red cons with my Druid, I find that anything above a White con will give me too many resists when soloing my Mage. Having a spell resisted, draws just as much agro as landing it so when you have to recast that DoT or Nuke, you run the chance of stealing agro from your pet. And you don't want that.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
