    <item>
      <title>Re: Magician class: Wow!</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=TNZ&amp;message.id=199570#M199570</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT face=Garamond&gt;&lt;FONT size=1&gt;&lt;SPAN class=""&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT face=Garamond size=1&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=1&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;Mages are a great soloing class - especially at the lower levels.&amp;nbsp; But the game changes a bit as you get into the higher end.&amp;nbsp; Eventually grouping with other players will become the only way to gain significant xp...and mages arent&amp;nbsp;always&amp;nbsp;a preferred class for an xp group.&amp;nbsp; In choosing a character you first need to choose if you like to tank, dps, heal, or utility.&amp;nbsp; If you like tanking choose warrior, dps choose rogue, heal choose cleric, utility depends on if you wish to be crowd control or enhance your group with buffs.&amp;nbsp; Of course there are classes which combine the abilities of others.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;If you want to tank but also want to have some group utility/ability to solo&amp;nbsp;you can choose to be a paladin (heals/buffs) or shadowknight (FD pulling/group mana at high levels).&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;Dps with utility would be monk (puller), ranger (root/snare/attack buffs/moderate ranged damage), beserker (similar abilities to ranger but less utility, more melee dps focus), Mage (primary attack in the form of nukes...pets and ds, if the tank allows ds, help sustain dps), Beastlord (primary attack in the form of melee...similar to mage with pet, can do basic "shaman" abilities), Necromancer (primary attack in the form of DoTs/nukes, pet to sustain dps, utility in the form of snares/group mana), Wizard (nuker, utility in teleports/punts).&amp;nbsp; Note that in the high end game many mobs resist nukes.&amp;nbsp; The effectiveness of nuking dps becomes sketchy in comparison to melee.&amp;nbsp; Mages and Necros have an advantage over wizards since they have meleeing pets, and mages ds/necros DoTs to deal some dps if nukes are resisted - often, pets are not allowed by Raid Leaders in large raids however.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;Healers with utility are druids (ports, large variety of buffs, nukes, DoTs - possibly the most well rounded class), shamans (primarily utility in the form of group/raid enhancement buffs).&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;More pure utility classes are Enchanters (most effective mezzers, important buffs, slow), and shamans (best slowers, and for buffs)...and Bards provide songs with unique properties to the bard class which make them valuable (can also mez and slow).&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;You should choose your class based on what you expect to be doing in EQ.&amp;nbsp; If you plan on leveling to 70+ and joining a raiding guild (while raiding guilds accept all classes for good reason) there are some classes which you may enjoy more in the high end.&amp;nbsp; For example, your mage won’t be able to solo as effectively at lvl 70 as it can at level 10.&amp;nbsp; Now, if you don’t ever plan on reaching level 70, and simply play eq for the fun of soloing in the lower level zones then mage might be the best choice...but don’t assume your interests in EQ wont change, as they likely will.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;Mage, similar to any class is a fine choice for the end game...but expect your role and playstyle to change.&amp;nbsp; With a changed role/playstyle you may lose interest in the mage you spend countless hours leveling, which can be devastating.&amp;nbsp; Burn out and loss of interest can ensue in having to start the xp grind all over again with a new character.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;I wish you luck in finding a class&amp;nbsp;that fits your interest in EQ.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;(&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;Forgive usual font size, my browser doesn’t like the soe forums &amp;gt;&amp;lt;)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
