      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Someone once quoted "My level 57 wizard takes nearly an entire bar of mana to kill a mob that gives decent xp."&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I've got a lvl 67 magician now, and can solo dark blues almost non stop with very little mana usage. I am sure I am not the only one, so maybe the poster of that comment needs to address either how much they nuke or how little they let their pet do the work.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I normally malos the mob back to my pull spot, then send in the pet , making sure it has taunt on. I then wait til mobs about 80% life and toss in my best rain spell. One, maybe two heals on the pet, and one final bolt nuke to finish mob off as he runs is all it takes most of the time. If I am very lucky with getting critical nukes, I can finish a fight with 80% of my mana or more left.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Or maybe the problem is the comment part about "decent exp". If i can get 2% aa on a mob ( I reserve normal exp for fast pull groups, if I can get them ) soloing, and it takes me about a minute to kill the mob, I chalk that up to being decent experience. But since we all have our own definition of decent experience, take that as you may.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Vorpal&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
